S → for ( INIT ; COND ; INC )

INIT → TYPE ID = NUM

COND → ID RELOP NUM

INC → ID INCOP

TYPE → int | float | char

RELOP → < | > | <= | >= | == | !=

INCOP → ++ | --

This CFG defines the structure of a C++ for loop
It ensures correct order: initialization, condition, increment
Each component is broken into smaller rules
